FORMER Botswana coach Major David Bright has passed on at the age of 65. The former army major reportedly succumbed to Covid-19 related complications at the Sir Ketumile Masire Hospital in Gaborone on Monday evening. Bright is considered to be one of Botswanaâ€™s most successful coaches having led Mogoditshane Fighters to three consecutive Botswana Premier League titles between 1999 and 2001. He also managed Engen Santos, Bay United, Gaborone United and Bay United during his illustrious coaching career. Bright also had numerous spells in charge of the Zebras with his latest ending on 19 February 2019 following an unsuccessful 2019 Africa Cup of Nations qualification campaign. 